fr.sorbonne_u.cps.map.interfaces

Interface MapCI<K extends java.io.Serializable,V extends java.io.Serializable>

  • All Superinterfaces:
    fr.sorbonne_u.components.interfaces.ComponentInterface, MapImplementationI<K,V>, fr.sorbonne_u.components.interfaces.OfferedCI, java.rmi.Remote, fr.sorbonne_u.components.interfaces.RequiredCI
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    MapConnector, MapInboundPort, MapInboundPortForPlugin, MapOutboundPort

    public interface MapCI<K extends java.io.Serializable,V extends java.io.Serializable>
extends fr.sorbonne_u.components.interfaces.OfferedCI, fr.sorbonne_u.components.interfaces.RequiredCI, MapImplementationI<K,V>
    The component interface MapCI declares the signatures of services to be offered by a map component and required by its clients.

    Description

    Nota: since Java 8, Oracle jdk release 241, methods inherited by a remote interface are no longer considered remote if the inherited interface is not itself remote; to bypass this, methods must be redefined in the remote method. Marking them with @Override stresses the design objective to share identical signatures between the implementation interface and the component interface.

    Invariant

     invariant              true

    Created on : 2019-03-21

    Author:
    Jacques Malenfant
